<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="860" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123R27/14: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul in Chargé at Shanghai</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-16T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            16, 1920—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>If Spiker has reached Shanghai in matter of Chang Ching-yao, in
                                struct him to return to Peking and leave investigation entirely in
                                    <pb facs="0912" n="814" xml:id="pg_814"/> hands of Consulate. If
                                Chang is in Shanghai report fact to Legation with request that
                                Legation ask Chinese Government to institute proceedings for his
                                arrest and trial.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>